94","1260":"1260","1160":"1160","Europa":"Europe","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Malaspina","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Tino, Aldo, Antonio, Carmella, Guido, Mario.","Italian:","from <i>mala</i> (feminine of <i>malo</i>) ‘bad, evil’ + <i>spina</i> ‘thorn’, applied as a nickname and personal name."],"variants":[{"name":"La Spina","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Sal, Angelo, Mario, Rosario, Sebastiano, Carmelo, Gino, Giuseppe, Ignazio, Javier, Orazio, Salvatore.","Italian (southern):","from <i>spina</i> ‘thorn’ (from Latin <i>spina</i>), with the definite article <i>la</i>, applied as a topographic name for someone who lived by a thorn bush or in an area of scrubland, or (in a transferred sense) for someone who lived by the crest or ridge of a hill. It could also be a nickname for a tall, thin, spiky person."]},{"name":"Spina","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Salvatore, Ciro, Antonio, Carmine, Angelo, Rocco, Vito, Carlo, Carmela, Santo, Vincenza, Vincenzo.","Italian:","from <i>spina</i> ‘thorn, thorn bush’, used as a nickname in various senses, including ‘distress, sorrow’ (alluding to Christ's crown of thorns), and also as a personal name; or alternatively a habitational name from any of numerous places called with this word (in some instances with reference to the dedication of a shrine)."]}]},{"name":"Tommaso","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament.  See  <b>Thomas</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Thomas","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Marchese Tommaso Malaspina was born about 1130 as the son of Marchese Federico Malaspina di Villafranca and Agnese del Bosco. He had at least 1 son with Richilda di Fosdinovo. He died in Europe."},"et":{"aproximadamente 1130–":"umbes 1130–Surnud","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","1200–1294":"1200–1294","–1301":"–1301","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","–1264":"–1264","–1260":"–1260","aproximadamente 1130":"umbes 1130","1301":"1301","1200":"1200","aproximadamente 1160":"umbes 1160","1264":"1264","1130":"1130","1294":"1294","1260":"1260","1160":"1160","Europa":"Europe"},"fi":{"aproximadamente 1130–":"noin 1130–Kuollut","1130–Male":"1130–Kuollut","1200–1294":"1200–1294","–1301":"–1301","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","–1264":"–1264","–1260":"–1260","aproximadamente 1130":"noin 1130","1301":"1301","1200":"1200","aproximadamente 1160":"noin 1160","1264":"1264","1130":"1130","1294":"1294","1260":"1260","1160":"1160","Europa":"Europe"},"fr":{"aproximadamente 1130–":"environ 1130–Décédé","1130–Male":"1130–Décédé","1200–1294":"1200–1294","–1301":"–1301","–Female":"Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1130–Female":"1130–Décédée","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","–1264":"–1264","–1260":"–1260","aproximadamente 1130":"environ 1130","1301":"1301","1200":"1200","aproximadamente 1160":"environ 1160","1264":"1264","1130":"1130","1294":"1294","1260":"1260","1160":"1160","Europa":"Europe","lifeSummary":"Marchese Tommaso Malaspina est né environ 1130, fils de Marchese Federico Malaspina di Villafranca et Agnese del Bosco. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Richilda di Fosdinovo. Il est décédé à Europe."},"de":{"aproximadamente 1130–":"um 1130–Verstorben","1130–Male":"1130–Verstorben","1200–1294":"1200–1294","–1301":"–1301","–Female":"Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1130–Female":"1130–Verstorben","1160–Male":"1